{
  "id": "MGASA-2021-0229",
  "summary": "Updated lz4 packages fix a security vulnerability",
  "details": "An attacker who submits a crafted file to an application linked with lz4 may be able to trigger an integer overflow, leading to calling of memmove() on a negative size argument, causing an out-of-bounds write and/or a crash. The greatest impact of this flaw is to availability, with some potential impact to confidentiality and integrity as well (CVE-2021-3520).\n",
